        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 13 at 11:14AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>A band of moderate to heavy snow lifting north late this morning
will reduce visibilities to generally 1 to 3 miles, with localized
reductions to as low as half of a mile. In addition to reductions
in visibility grassy surfaces could see snowfall accumulations of
a quarter to half of an inch over the next hour.

Travelers should be prepared for reductions in visibility, along
with slush accumulations on elevated surfaces like bridges. Slow
down, allow extra time to reach your destination, and allow extra
spacing between vehicles.
</description>
